As of the [[census]]<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=DEC_10_PL_GCTPL2.ST13&prodType=table United States Census]{{dead link|bot=medic|date=April 2020}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> of 2010, there were 158 people living in the CDP. The [[population density]] was 254.2 people per square mile. The racial makeup of the CDP was 37% [[Race (United States Census)|White]] and 63% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]]. 96% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

